The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Models urged to be wary

 London, Feb. 20 (Reuters): The government is warning aspiring models and entertainers to be on their guard against rogue casting agencies who try to relieve them of their money on the false promise of fame.

 The department of trade and industry has published advice to help would-be entertainers and models ensure that they work with reputable agencies. The move follows several cases where agencies have advertised casting sessions in local newspapers, then used hard-sell tactics to take payments from candidates on promises of success and stardom. 




